trans-unit.source:
Interesting facts! I am a Brazilian graduated Computer Engineer. I love coding, playing guitar and Brazil. I also LOVE coffee. I knew my vocation since I was 14 years old. At my time at the University, I collaborated in an international project called Butterfly that became my Term paper at the end of the course.
After 5 years working at Rodrimar, I had 3 different positions: IT-Internship, Technical Support Analyst and System Analyst. During my time in there I was able to gaining a wide knowledge that I consider decisive. At this moment, I'm based in Hamburg learning German and studying to stay up to date with the latest programming languages and trying to increment my working experience in another country.
